1.Local Variable
             -Declare inside a method.
             -only accessible within that block.
Example:
void Localvariable() {
    int a = 100; 
    System.out.println(a);
}
2.Instance Variable
             -Declared inside a class but outside methods
             -Belong to each object
Example:
class Staticvariable(){
    String name;
}
3.Static Variable
            -Declared using the static keyword.
            -Shared by all objects of the class.
Example:
static String name="abcdef";
4.Paramater variable
            -Declared inside the parentheses of a method.
            -Used to pass data into the method
Example":
class Example {
    void Parametervariable(String name) {
        System.out.println( name);
    }
